\begin_layout Subsection
Equilibirum with Factors of Production
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Constant returns to scale means - 
\begin_inset Formula $zY=F(zK,zL)$
\end_inset

 for the output production function 
\begin_inset Formula $Y=F(K,L)$
\end_inset

.
 Labour costs are 
\begin_inset Formula $WL$
\end_inset

 and capital costs
\begin_inset Formula $RK$
\end_inset

 where (
\begin_inset Formula $W$
\end_inset

 is wage and 
\begin_inset Formula $R$
\end_inset

 is the rental price of capital - i.e.
 borrowing costs).
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{alignat}{1}
Profit & =P\cdot F(K,L)-WL-RK\label{eq:profit}
\end{alignat}

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula $MPL=F(K,L+1)-F(K,L)=\frac{\partial F}{\partial L}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $MPK=F(K+1,L)-F(K,L)=\frac{\partial F}{\partial K}$
\end_inset

.
 Using 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "eq:profit"

\end_inset

, Profit wrt Labour thus changes as 
\begin_inset Formula $\Delta Profit=P\cdot MPL-W$
\end_inset

 (labor doesn't change with respect to capital in the short run).
 The equilibrium is achieved when 
\begin_inset Formula $dProfit=0$
\end_inset

:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{alignat}{1}
MPL & =\frac{{W}}{P}
\end{alignat}

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Similarly, we can 
\begin_inset Formula $dProfit=P\cdot MPK-R=0$
\end_inset

 implies that 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{alignat}{1}
MPK & =\frac{R}{P}
\end{alignat}

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Notice that only every variable except 
\begin_inset Formula $K,L$
\end_inset

 is exogenous in the above model and that the equilibrium is achieved when
 economic profit is 0.
 The combined effect can be written using 
\begin_inset Formula $dF=\frac{\partial F}{\partial L}dL+\frac{\partial F}{\partial K}dK$
\end_inset

 as 
\begin_inset Formula $dProfit=PdF-WdL-RdK=(P\frac{\partial F}{\partial L}-W)dL+(P\frac{\partial F}{\partial K}-R)dK=0$
\end_inset

 at equilibrium.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Note that since most employers/companies own capital rather than rent it
 the accounting profit includes their return on capital (
\begin_inset Formula $MPK\cdot K)$
\end_inset

 as well.
\end_layout

